reviews.text: Sashimi was really bad, can totally cause food poisoning if consumed, and the manager seems fine to be serving that to us. Service was way below standard of the other restaurants in the same chain. Need to improve a lot to live up the reputation.
Quite close to Japanese local tastes. Clean and cozy sitting environment.
Value for money, considering it's located in a shopping centre.  Food was great, friendly service
Waited for ages for table for four and the food was good (maybe I was starving because of long wait!). Ok service but could be better.

Restaurant only had half a dozen or so tables full, came in for a light snack and ordered 3 dishes, took an hour to get after asking a few times for our final dish. Servers kept servicing other guests while we were left with empty tea cups after asking for more tea while waiting for our last dish.

result.name: 大戶屋

reviews.text: 價錢服務都不及日本好（香港地不能要求有日本水準的期望啊），不過整體都比香港其他日式餐廳好，同行的人都覺得不錯。晚飯時段排隊人數多，要早點去排。
兩人午餐選項多，也十分抵食，份量及質量均佳，而且也可選飲梅酒(小瓶原樽奉上)梳打，極之可口，有原梅子兩枚。魚及牛舌也很有水準，冷烏東吃後也減去炎熱帶來的悶熱，甜品也是必須嘗試。
家庭式日本菜！  取價公道理！  但有時味道偏咸
侍應服務有待改善，不過食物cp值高

reviews.text: Huge shopping mall with lots of outlets and plenty of things to do. Worth a visit if you are relaxing in Tsuen Wan and just want some place to kill time, or if you're out to shop till you drop and come home with a haul. Food options are also plenty, but nothing novel - look at it as refueling opportunities rather than experiences.
Nice mall where you can spend a day for shopping and eating
Fully car parking. No good restaurant. Forget this mall and never come again
An pretty good shopping mall in a convenient location in Tsuen Wan, interconnected with other major malls in the area.
Spacious with a bunch of mid-range shops. Some great eateries there too. Overall a cheerful place.
